devpkg

devpkg is a small source package installer written in C.

It can:
- initialize a local package database
- list installed package URLs
- fetch source archives
- build source code from /tmp/pkg-build
- install packages from URLs
- process DEPENDS files

Usage:

	./devpkg -S

Initialize the database directory and database file.

	./devpkg -L

List installed package URLs.

	./devpkg -I URL

Fetch, build, install, and record a package URL.

EXamples:
	./devpkg -I http://example.com/package.tar.gz
	./devpkg -I http://example.com/package.tar.bz2
	./devpkg -I git://example.com/project.git

	./devpkg -F URL

Fetch source only. This downloads or prepares the source, but does not build or install it.

	./devpkg -B URL

Build and install form the exsisting build directory.

	./devpkg -c OPTS

Pass options to ./configure.

Example:
	./devpkg -I http://example.com/package.tar.gz -c --prefix=/usr/local

	./devpkg -m OPTS

Pass options to make.

Example:
	./devpkg -I http://example.com/package.tar.gz -m -j4

	./devpkg -i TARGET

Pass a target to make through sudo make TARGET.

Example:
	./devpkg -I http://example.com/package.tar.gz -i install

Typical install flow:

	./devpkg -S
	./devpkg -I URL
	./devpkg -L

Notes:

- devpkg stores installed package URLs in /usr/loacl/.devpkg/db.
- Temporary build files are stored in /tmp/pkg-build.
- Downloaded tarballs are stored temporarily in /tmp/pkg-src.tar.gz or /tmp/pkg-src-tar-bz2.
- DEPENDS files are downloaded temporarily to /tmp/DEPENDS.
- Commands such as curl, git, tar, make, and sudo must be available.
